**Prompt:**

> I'm an intern learning how we compute theoretical prices for options and stocks here. I need you to explore the actual codebase (not describe generic option pricing theory) and produce a rigorous internal-implementation writeup. Please:
>
> 1. **Locate the relevant code**: Search for pricing modules — terms like "theo," "theoretical price," "fair value," "pricer," "Black-Scholes," "binomial," "BSM," or ticker/instrument-keyed pricing services. List every file path you find before summarizing anything.
>
> 2. **Pricing model(s) used**: Identify which model(s) are actually implemented — Black-Scholes-Merton, binomial/trinomial trees, local vol, stochastic vol (Heston/SABR), or a proprietary variant — and show the exact formulas as coded, not textbook versions. Flag any approximations, closed-form shortcuts, or numerical methods (finite difference, Monte Carlo) used instead of analytic solutions.
