> 8. **Where it's used downstream**: Find what consumes these theoretical prices — quoting engines, risk systems, P&L attribution, edge/alpha calculations.
>
> 9. **Deviations from textbook models**: Explicitly flag any place the code diverges from standard financial theory for practical reasons (e.g., vol surface smoothing hacks, discrete dividend handling, early-exercise approximations for American options).
